<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870813-0149 </DOCNO><HL> McDonnell Douglas U.S. Jobs</HL><DD> 08/13/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MD BA ROKDEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Units of McDonnell Douglas Corp. got contracts totaling $20.8 million for Harpoon cruise missile-engineering services for the Air Force and AH64 helicopter improvements for the Army.    Units of Boeing Co. were awarded Air Force contracts totaling $15.5 million for MX missile-engineering services and B-1B aircraft test equipment.    Rockwell International Corp. won a $10.9 million Air Force contract for aircraft communications and navigation equipment. </TEXT></DOC>